Analysis of the Main Target Image
--------------------------------
There are two separate “sub‐structures” in the scene:

(1) Left Sub‐Structure (9 blocks total; effectively one layer):
•  A central green square block with four blue square blocks snugly around its four edges (forming a plus‐shaped top when viewed from above).  
•  Four orange wedge blocks are placed around the perimeter beneath/alongside the blue blocks, sloping outward.  
•  Altogether, this sub‐structure is one layer high but uses 9 individual pieces (1 green + 4 blue + 4 orange wedges).

(2) Right Sub‐Structure (7 blocks total; four layers if stacked bottom‐to‐top):
•  Bottom Layer: Two red arch blocks (one toward the front, one toward the rear).  
•  Second Layer: A green rectangular block bridging across the red arches.  
•  Third Layer: A wide yellow rectangular block sitting on the green block.  
•  Top Layer: An orange cylinder standing upright in the center, flanked on left and right by two orange wedge blocks.  
•  This sub‐structure thus uses 7 individual pieces (2 red arches + 1 green rectangular + 1 yellow rectangular + 2 orange wedges + 1 orange cylinder).

Block Selection From the Dictionary
-----------------------------------
Below are exactly which dictionary blocks (by index) match the target in both shape/orientation and color.  
Remember: no orientation changes are allowed beyond what is shown in the dictionary.

•  Left Sub‐Structure (9 blocks):
   –  Center green cube: index 3 (×1)  
   –  Blue cubes around center: index 2 (×4)  
   –  Orange wedges around perimeter: index 16 (×4)

•  Right Sub‐Structure (7 blocks):
   –  Red arches (base): index 1 (×2)  
   –  Green rectangular block: index 6 (×1)  
   –  Yellow rectangular block: index 7 (×1)  
   –  Orange wedges (top ring): index 12 (×2)  
   –  Orange cylinder (vertical): index 9 (×1)

Step‐by‐Step Assembly Order
---------------------------
Below is one possible assembly sequence (Steps 1–16).  

{
  Step1:  Move block with index 3        // Place green cube (left structure center)
  Step2:  Move block with index 2        // 1st blue cube around the green
  Step3:  Move block with index 2        // 2nd blue cube around the green
  Step4:  Move block with index 2        // 3rd blue cube around the green
  Step5:  Move block with index 2        // 4th blue cube around the green
  Step6:  Move block with index 16       // 1st orange wedge (left structure)
  Step7:  Move block with index 16       // 2nd orange wedge (left structure)
  Step8:  Move block with index 16       // 3rd orange wedge (left structure)
  Step9:  Move block with index 16       // 4th orange wedge (left structure)
  Step10: Move block with index 1        // 1st red arch (right structure base)
  Step11: Move block with index 1        // 2nd red arch (right structure base)
  Step12: Move block with index 6        // Green rectangular atop red arches
  Step13: Move block with index 7        // Yellow rectangular on the green block
  Step14: Move block with index 12       // 1st orange wedge (top ring)
  Step15: Move block with index 12       // 2nd orange wedge (top ring)
  Step16: Move block with index 9        // Orange cylinder in center
}
